snippet.textDisplay: I absolutely loved every second of it. It was so beautifully sung and merged that I wanted to hear more and more of it. I am so excited to see Hassan Jahangir in Coke Studio. He was the man that initiated the rise of pop music in Pakistan so thanks for including him. I am ecstatic that you gave Rachel a song as well. Hopefully in the next season we can also hear the beautiful voice of Shabnam Majeed because I have never loved anyone's voice the way I love hers so do include her in the next season. There is a young melodious girl named Rose mary Mushtaq that truly deserves an opportunity to sing on this platform. Her voice is breathtaking and reminds me of a nightingale so please give her a chance next year. I also want to hear Maria Meer on Coke Studio so badly. She's an incredibly talented girl and after hearing her gorgeous voice, I can't wait for her to join your team next year. I am so proud of the diversity in this season including the represention of the transgender community as well. I am proud of our rich cultural heritage that has been so elegantly showcased by Coke Studio Pakistan. Pakistani music is incomparable and more special than any music I have heard in my life. Keep exploring raw talent and keep making us proud by producing such breathtaking melodies. Lots of love from a Pakistani.
